# Read the data to DataSet
library(readr)
DataSet <- read_csv("./BUS_OTP_DATA.csv")
print(DataSet)
## # A tibble: 180 × 5
##    OTP_YEAR OTP_MONTH   OTP TOTAL_TRIPS TOTAL_LATES
##       <dbl> <chr>     <dbl>       <dbl>       <dbl>
##  1     2009 Jan        92.8       34119        2464
##  2     2009 Feb        92.8       31932        2300
##  3     2009 Mar        92.2       34065        2645
##  4     2009 Apr        92.8       35134        2524
##  5     2009 May        92.8       32451        2349
##  6     2009 Jun        94.8       34731        1810
##  7     2009 Jul        94.1       34596        2040
##  8     2009 Aug        94.4       33953        1890
##  9     2009 Sep        93         34198        2398
## 10     2009 Oct        94.6       36034        1939
## # ℹ 170 more rows
# Process the normalization between years firstly.
for (i in 2009:2023){
  means <- colMeans(DataSet[DataSet$OTP_YEAR==i,3:5])
  DataSet[DataSet$OTP_YEAR==i,3] <- DataSet[DataSet$OTP_YEAR==i,3] - means[1]+92.4
  DataSet[DataSet$OTP_YEAR==i,4] <- DataSet[DataSet$OTP_YEAR==i,4] - means[2]+42222.8
  DataSet[DataSet$OTP_YEAR==i,5] <- DataSet[DataSet$OTP_YEAR==i,5] - means[3]+3188.37244
}
numDataset <- DataSet[,3:5]

# Check the correlations between different columns
cor(numDataset)
##                     OTP TOTAL_TRIPS TOTAL_LATES
## OTP          1.00000000  0.09289877  -0.8615492
## TOTAL_TRIPS  0.09289877  1.00000000   0.3764204
## TOTAL_LATES -0.86154924  0.37642045   1.0000000
# Process the PCA
busPCA <- prcomp(numDataset,scale=TRUE)
busPCA
## Standard deviations (1, .., p=3):
## [1] 1.3816701 1.0333711 0.1520914
## 
## Rotation (n x k) = (3 x 3):
##                    PC1        PC2        PC3
## OTP          0.6569412 -0.3949667  0.6422069
## TOTAL_TRIPS -0.2301643 -0.9161988 -0.3280307
## TOTAL_LATES -0.7179504 -0.0676838  0.6927959
summary(busPCA)
## Importance of components:
##                           PC1    PC2     PC3
## Standard deviation     1.3817 1.0334 0.15209
## Proportion of Variance 0.6363 0.3559 0.00771
## Cumulative Proportion  0.6363 0.9923 1.00000
# Some analysis about the PCs, include eigenvalues, variance percentage and povit

(eigen_bus <- busPCA$sdev^2)
## [1] 1.90901230 1.06785589 0.02313181
names(eigen_bus) <- paste("PC",1:3,sep="")
sumlambdas <- sum(eigen_bus)
propvar <- eigen_bus/sumlambdas
cumvar_bus <- cumsum(propvar)
matlambdas <- rbind(eigen_bus,propvar,cumvar_bus)
rownames(matlambdas) <- c("Eigenvalues","Variance","Accumulative variance")
round(matlambdas,4)
##                          PC1    PC2    PC3
## Eigenvalues           1.9090 1.0679 0.0231
## Variance              0.6363 0.3560 0.0077
## Accumulative variance 0.6363 0.9923 1.0000

## Standard deviations (1, .., p=3):

## Rotation (n x k) = (3 x 3):
##                    PC1        PC2        PC3

## TOTAL_TRIPS -0.2301643 -0.9161988 -0.3280307
## TOTAL_LATES -0.7179504 -0.0676838  0.6927959
# Here, I want to keep PC1 and PC2, because the sum or their variance can explain 99%.
# For each PC, here is the formula:
# PC1 = 0.6569 * OTP - 0.2301 * TOTAL_TRIPS - 0.7180 * TOTAL_LATES
# PC2 = -0.3950 * OTP - 0.9162 * TOTAL_TRIPS - 0.3280 * TOTAL_LATES
# PC3 = 0.6422 * OTP - 0.3280 * TOTAL_TRIPS + 0.6928 * TOTAL_LATES
# Visualization of PCs
library(factoextra)
library(FactoMineR)
library(ggfortify)
library(psych)
library(corrplot)
library(devtools)

# Correlation
pairs.panels(DataSet[3:5],
             gap = 0,
             bg = c("red", "blue")[DataSet$OTP_MONTH],
             pch=21)

pairs.panels(busPCA$x,
             gap=0,
             bg = c("red", "blue")[DataSet$OTP_MONTH],
             pch=21)

fviz_eig(busPCA, addlabels = TRUE)

fviz_pca_var(busPCA,col.var = "cos2",
             gradient.cols = c("#FFCC00", "#CC9933", "#660033", "#330033"),
             repel = TRUE)

fviz_pca_ind(busPCA, col.ind = "cos2", 
                  gradient.cols = c("#FFCC00", "#CC9933", "#660033", "#330033"), 
                  repel = TRUE)

biplot(busPCA)

autoplot(busPCA,
         data = DataSet[3:5],
         loadings = TRUE,
         labels = DataSet$OTP_MONTH)
